requests.name: Retrieve business objects using the specified parameters
requests.description: This method provides searches for business objects within the database.  The results for searching on a time stamp field are affected by the way that DB2Â® handles time stamps. The JSON string uses ISO format for time stamps, such as 2016-06-15T20:11:19.326-04:00. DB2 converts this value to 2016-06-15-20.11.19.326000. Because DB2 might add more precision by storing a time stamp as 2016-06-15-20.11.19.326nnnn, the search results might not return what is expected. Refer to your DB2 documentation

queryParams.description: Userid / password for user with appropriate role
A valid business object type.
The starting index of the matching records to return. This is a 0-based value. For example, a value of 3 would return results starting at the fourth matching record.
Prominence level of the fields that you want returned.  A prominence value is required for each logical object field when the business object is created.
The number of matching records to return.
